  "texts": [
    "The perception of risk is often seen as the major barrier to user adoption of innovative technologies (Wang et al., 2018).",
    "In virtual worlds such as the metaverse, protecting user privacy and ensuring data security is an extremely important matter (Lee et al., 2021).",
    "Data in the metaverse serves as the primary form of governance, paving the way for collecting increasingly specific information from users (e.g., transactions, physical state, facial images) (Zhao et al., 2022).",
    "Despite the metaverse showing promise, the key challenges that hinder its sustained growth are issues related to security and privacy (Wang et al., 2022b).",
    "Managing massive streams of data, the prevalence of users' profiling activities, and unfair outcomes of AI-based algorithms are just some of the potential security defects and privacy invasions that that have the potential to take place in the metaverse."
